// Presence: who's online right now.
//
// In-memory only on the server — presence state does not persist
// across server restarts. Subscriptions are session-scoped and
// evaporate on disconnect.
//
// Two orthogonal axes:
//   - activity:   what the user is doing (ONLINE | AWAY)
//   - visibility: whether it's broadcast (VISIBLE | INVISIBLE)
//
// The projected state emitted to subscribers folds both axes down
// to one PresenceState enum: an INVISIBLE user appears as OFFLINE
// to others, regardless of their activity.
//
// Own sessions see their TRUE state (ONLINE/AWAY/INVISIBLE) for
// multi-device sync via OwnPresenceChanged. Other subscribers see
// the masked projection via PresenceChanged.
//
// Blocks interact with presence: if a block exists between viewer
// and target (either direction), the viewer sees the target as
// OFFLINE always. Same DM-gate policy chat already enforces.

